WEBVTT

00:02.086 --> 00:05.546
Here's what's happened on Glee if you
live in a cave or just got out of prison.

00:05.631 --> 00:07.632
- Will took over the Glee Club.
At first they were terrible.
- We suck.

00:07.716 --> 00:11.427
But then they got kind of good.
Quinn got pregnant and said
it was Finn's but it was Puck's.

00:11.512 --> 00:14.097
- I'm done with you!
- And Will's wife, Terri,
said she was pregnant.

00:14.181 --> 00:17.183
- But she was just scared
that Will liked Emma.
- I just left my wife.

00:17.267 --> 00:19.018
- And then they kissed.
- I want you to be happy, Finn.

00:19.103 --> 00:21.270
Rachel loves that she and Finn
are the Glee Club's new power couple.

00:21.355 --> 00:24.774
But he seems weird about it. Sue tried
to throw sectionals, but they won anyway.

00:24.858 --> 00:28.319
- Which is pretty exciting.
- This is a travesty
of international proportions.

00:28.404 --> 00:29.946
That's what you missed on Glee.

00:32.658 --> 00:35.118
[School Bell Rings]
[Chattering]

00:39.623 --> 00:43.042
Hey, babe.
Looking good.
Feeling good, Mercedes.

00:43.127 --> 00:45.378
This is amazing. Ever since
Glee Club won sectionals,

00:45.462 --> 00:47.380
everybody looks at us differently.

00:47.506 --> 00:50.007
I wanna be
with you, Rachel.
We're glitterati.

00:50.134 --> 00:53.302
I feel like Lady Gaga.
Get used to it, guys.
We're stars now,

00:53.387 --> 00:55.680
on par with all the jocks
and popular kids.

00:55.764 --> 00:57.724
It's the dawn of a new era
here at McKinley,

00:57.808 --> 00:59.809
and we are gonna rule this school.

01:01.353 --> 01:03.354
Ooh-hoo. Welcome to Loser Town.

01:03.439 --> 01:05.356
Population: You.

01:05.441 --> 01:08.234
But I don't understand. We won sectionals.

01:08.318 --> 01:10.319
I've completely demonstrated
the validity of this program.

01:10.404 --> 01:13.322
Now you're saying we have to place
at regionals or the Glee Club's gone?

01:13.407 --> 01:16.242
Schue, that was the deal
from the beginning.

01:16.326 --> 01:21.122
I still have a bottom line.
Those spotlights in the auditorium
don't run on dreams.

01:21.206 --> 01:23.583
Our electricity consumption
is up two percent.

01:23.667 --> 01:26.085
Besides, it's cold out, Schue,

01:26.170 --> 01:28.921
and the Cheerios can no longer
practice out of doors.

01:29.006 --> 01:31.007
They need the use
of the auditorium as well.

01:31.091 --> 01:33.259
But the Cheerios
don't even have a coach.

01:33.343 --> 01:36.053
[Sue]
Oh, yes, they do.

01:36.138 --> 01:38.473
Hey, buddy,
you get a haircut? Looks awful.

01:38.599 --> 01:42.518
What are you doing here?
I'm just dropping off
a mocha for my maharishi.

01:42.603 --> 01:45.438
I took the liberty
of making it a double whip.

01:45.522 --> 01:48.483
Because after our conciliatory dinner,

01:48.567 --> 01:51.194
I happen to know that there is nothing...

01:51.278 --> 01:53.571
you won't eat whipped cream off of.

01:53.655 --> 01:55.865
[Blowing]

01:57.075 --> 01:59.410
Would've gotten you one, Will,
but I don't like you.

02:00.704 --> 02:02.538
Okay.

02:03.832 --> 02:06.501
Okay, what the hell is going on here?

02:06.585 --> 02:09.545
You suspended her
after she leaked our set list to sectionals.

02:09.630 --> 02:13.758
Yes, and the point
of suspension is reinstatement.

02:13.842 --> 02:16.719
[Pushing Buttons]

02:16.804 --> 02:19.055
[Crowd Cheering]

02:23.936 --> 02:26.103
[Finn's Voice] In some ways,
I'm happy football season's over.

02:26.188 --> 02:31.776
I did set the single-season record for being
sacked, but we only won one game.

02:31.860 --> 02:35.321
So I'm hoping basketball
can be a fresh start.

02:39.910 --> 02:42.703
The fact is, I'm kind of depressed.

02:42.788 --> 02:43.955
Hey!

02:44.039 --> 02:45.414
- Hey, Finn.
- Oh.

02:45.499 --> 02:47.625
I made us
his-and-her relationship calendars.

02:47.709 --> 02:49.710
That way, we always know
what the other is up to,

02:49.795 --> 02:52.088
so you can't say you forgot we had plans
when you miss our dates anymore.

02:52.172 --> 02:54.090
Great. But I'm kind
of allergic to cats, so-

02:54.174 --> 02:56.717
I filled in all of our dates
for the next month.

02:56.802 --> 03:00.012
On the sixth,
we're going to see Phantom
at the Autistic Children's Center.

03:00.097 --> 03:02.557
[Finn] I know I saved Glee Club,
and I guess chicks dig me,

03:02.641 --> 03:06.185
but I guess if I'm being honest,
it's more like I'm not over her.

03:06.270 --> 03:08.396
I'm not breaking up with you.
I'm just saying please stop super-sizing,

03:08.480 --> 03:10.773
'cause I don't dig on fat chicks.

03:10.899 --> 03:12.942
I'm pregnant.
And that's my fault?

03:13.026 --> 03:16.487
- And Rachel— now that we're sort of dating,
- [Chattering, Indistinct]

03:16.572 --> 03:18.781
I have to work so much harder
to pretend to be listening to her.

03:18.866 --> 03:21.284
That sounds great.

03:21.368 --> 03:24.245
Sometimes I wish I could be
more like Coach Tanaka.

03:24.329 --> 03:27.415
He pulled a Jessica Simpson.
You know, lost his fiancée,

03:27.499 --> 03:29.792
gained 40 pounds and stopped showering.

03:29.877 --> 03:31.794
And everyone acts like it's totally normal.

03:35.340 --> 03:37.592
- [Whistle Blows]
- [Buzzer Sounds]

03:37.676 --> 03:40.303
That's my boyfriend!

03:42.097 --> 03:45.641
I'm off my game, and I don't
know how to get back on it.

03:49.688 --> 03:52.189
[School Bell Rings]

03:56.278 --> 04:00.072
There. You no longer confuse me
with your she-male looks.

04:00.157 --> 04:03.159
I'm gonna donate this
to the victims of Hurricane Katrina.

04:03.243 --> 04:05.703
They can use it to plug
the holes in their trailers.

04:07.080 --> 04:08.998
Sue.

04:09.082 --> 04:11.792
Please tell me how you managed
to pull off getting reinstated.

04:11.877 --> 04:14.795
Well, William, I realized
back in my condo in Boca...

04:14.880 --> 04:17.548
that I had indeed behaved poorly.

04:17.633 --> 04:19.759
Riddled with remorse,
I arranged a dinner...

04:19.843 --> 04:22.720
so Figgins and I could have
a little professional sit-down.

04:22.804 --> 04:25.473
Sue, there's no way
I'm letting you back into that school.

04:25.557 --> 04:27.808
Mind flagging down that waiter?

04:29.353 --> 04:33.272
We had a very frank
and healing discussion.
And you know what, Will?

04:33.357 --> 04:38.527
It was like he was seeing me
and my moral integrity
for the very first time.

04:38.612 --> 04:41.489
[Siren Blaring]

04:44.034 --> 04:47.536
So here's what's gonna happen.
As of right now, I am reinstated.

04:47.663 --> 04:52.124
Or I will tell your wife
and the entire congregation
of the Cornerstone Bible Way Church...

04:52.209 --> 04:53.709
of our sexual congress.

04:53.794 --> 04:56.045
It's your choice.

04:56.129 --> 04:57.505
Smile.

04:59.383 --> 05:02.009
- Oh, God!
- Okay, look, Sue.

05:02.094 --> 05:04.095
If you’re back, let's bury the hatchet.

05:04.179 --> 05:05.972
I won't be burying
any hatchets, William,

05:06.056 --> 05:07.974
unless I happen to get
a clear shot to your groin.

05:08.058 --> 05:10.059
You humiliated me.

05:10.143 --> 05:12.103
You did this to yourself, Sue.

05:12.229 --> 05:15.564
All I did was enjoy
watching it happen.
Yeah, well, enjoy this, William.

05:15.649 --> 05:17.608
Now that I am back
and my position is secured,

05:17.693 --> 05:19.360
I will not stop until you are fired...

05:19.444 --> 05:22.154
and your little Glee Club
is annihilated into oblivion.

05:22.280 --> 05:25.408
Bring it.
Oh, I will bring it,
William.

05:25.492 --> 05:27.159
You know
what else I'm gonna bring?

05:27.244 --> 05:29.537
I'm gonna bring some Asian cookery
to rub your head with.

05:29.621 --> 05:32.957
'Cause right now,
you got enough product
in your hair to season a wok.

05:36.503 --> 05:38.421
[Sighs]

05:44.094 --> 05:45.594
Hello.

05:46.596 --> 05:48.973
- Hello?
- Hello.

05:49.057 --> 05:51.517
- What do you guys say
when you answer the phone?
- "What up?"

05:51.643 --> 05:54.270
"Who this be?"
"No. She's dead.
This is her son."

05:54.354 --> 05:57.898
O-kay. Alexander Graham Bell,
inventor of the telephone,

05:57.983 --> 06:00.609
liked to say "ahoy, ahoy"
when he answered the phone.

06:00.694 --> 06:05.489
It was Edison who decided that "hello"
was a more appropriate greeting.

06:05.574 --> 06:10.286
Look, I am really proud
of what you guys did at sectionals.

06:10.370 --> 06:12.288
But as most of you
have realized by now,

06:12.372 --> 06:14.790
it hasn't made a bit of difference
in your day-to-day at school.

06:14.875 --> 06:17.126
I have a Slushee-stained
training bra to prove it.

06:17.210 --> 06:19.211
The fact is,
we're gonna have to be better,

06:19.296 --> 06:22.214
even more spectacular
at regionals.

06:22.299 --> 06:25.384
It's time for some reinvention,
some new New Directions.

06:25.469 --> 06:29.013
We need a new... hello.

06:29.097 --> 06:30.890
Here's your assignment
for the week.

06:30.974 --> 06:35.644
Come up with a fresh number, but it has
to have "hello" in the song title. All right?

06:37.564 --> 06:39.356
