28:14.610 --> 28:17.320
♪ I'm on a highway to hell ♪

28:17.404 --> 28:20.990
- ♪ I'm on it
I'm on it ♪
- ♪ Highway to hell ♪

28:23.077 --> 28:24.786
♪ Don't stop me ♪

28:24.870 --> 28:27.288
♪ Oh, yeah ♪♪

28:27.289 --> 28:27.497
♪ Oh, yeah ♪♪

28:29.625 --> 28:32.794
Stop, please. Dear God, just stop.

28:32.878 --> 28:36.047
Seriously, guys,
it's like watching beige paint dry.

28:36.131 --> 28:40.843
Could everyone please look at Jesse?
Jesse, give us a show face.

28:40.928 --> 28:45.473
That's a show face, guys.
You wanna look so talented
it's literally hurting you.

28:45.557 --> 28:50.311
I want a look that's so optimistic,
it could cure cancer.

28:50.396 --> 28:54.023
That's what I'm talking about.
Take five, everybody. Drink a Red Bull.

28:56.735 --> 28:59.487
Uh, excuse me.
Ms. Corcoran? Hi. I'm Will Schuester.

28:59.571 --> 29:01.406
I'm sorry.
I don't know who you are.

29:01.490 --> 29:05.827
I'm a big fan, really.
I also coach the McKinley Glee Club.

29:05.911 --> 29:09.414
I don't usually cotton too well
to my competition sneaking in
to watch a rehearsal.

29:09.498 --> 29:12.500
But I also have trouble
seeing you guys as competition.

29:13.836 --> 29:16.045
I believe you have a student
named Jesse St. James?

29:16.130 --> 29:18.631
Yeah, I think he might be dating
one of my students.

29:18.715 --> 29:20.716
I'm more than a little concerned...

29:20.801 --> 29:24.011
with the whole fraternizing
with the enemy aspect of their relationship.

29:24.096 --> 29:26.013
You think we're spying on you?

29:26.098 --> 29:29.475
Honestly? Yes.

29:29.560 --> 29:32.728
Noted. Look,
I don't stand for any funny business,

29:32.813 --> 29:35.231
and Jesse's a good kid.

29:35.315 --> 29:38.818
What can you do?
The heart wants what the heart wants.

29:38.902 --> 29:42.321
Sometimes there's that little spark.

29:50.038 --> 29:53.749
I'm not interested
in coaching just your
average high school Glee Club.

29:53.876 --> 29:56.335
I'm driven
to excellence.
Yeah, excellence.

29:56.420 --> 29:58.504
A lot of people thought
I couldn't take nationals...

29:58.589 --> 30:01.632
with a routine where the kids
dance entirely on their hands.

30:01.717 --> 30:04.343
[Panting]

30:04.428 --> 30:06.387
Okay. Oh, no. I'm sorry.

30:07.431 --> 30:09.390
We have to stop. I-

30:11.226 --> 30:13.186
I just can't do this.

30:13.270 --> 30:16.314
Aw, I'm sorry. I'm all business.
I'm trying to work on that.

30:16.398 --> 30:18.274
No, it isn't that.

30:18.400 --> 30:22.028
Are you gay?
What? No.

30:22.112 --> 30:24.780
Because most
of the show choir directors
I make out with are gay.

30:28.869 --> 30:32.663
I spend every waking moment
thinking about Vocal Adrenaline.

30:32.748 --> 30:35.750
I have no life.
I haven't been on a date in three years.

30:35.876 --> 30:38.044
Here you go.
Thanks.

30:38.128 --> 30:40.713
I did lie to you earlier.

30:40.797 --> 30:44.133
I do know who you are.
I saw you at our fall invitational.

30:44.218 --> 30:47.136
- I thought you were really cute.
- [Chuckles]

30:47.221 --> 30:50.431
I know what you mean about
being obsessed with work.

30:50.516 --> 30:52.517
I'm so committed to the Glee Club,

30:52.601 --> 30:56.395
and I think it played a big part
in ending my marriage.

30:56.480 --> 30:58.689
How long have you been divorced?

30:58.774 --> 31:02.443
Um, well, I'm not really divorced yet.

31:02.528 --> 31:05.863
And then I-I started dating someone
I-I really care about,

31:05.948 --> 31:07.865
but it isn't working for some reason.

31:07.950 --> 31:12.036
Oh, you're already seeing someone else
and you were just making out with me.

31:12.120 --> 31:14.789
I'm kind of a mess.

31:14.873 --> 31:18.668
- Look, I don't wanna tell you
how to live your life.
- Please, be my guest.

31:18.752 --> 31:22.797
I think you need to take some time
to reintroduce yourself to yourself.

31:22.881 --> 31:26.509
You just finished
being somebody's husband,
and that didn't really work out.

31:26.593 --> 31:29.220
And now you're running off
to be somebody's boyfriend?

31:29.304 --> 31:31.514
Seems to me you need
to take a little breather.

31:31.598 --> 31:34.433
Look,

31:34.518 --> 31:39.814
that hair, that dimple,
that terrible clunker you drive-

31:39.898 --> 31:42.525
I think you're about
the cutest thing I've ever seen.

31:42.609 --> 31:45.319
Here's my number.

31:45.404 --> 31:47.989
When you get things
sorted out, give me a call.

31:48.073 --> 31:52.535
Thank you for the coffee.
And the making out? It's kind of hot.

32:00.961 --> 32:04.630
- [School Bell Rings]
- Hey, guys.

32:04.715 --> 32:08.676
Cut the butter, Benedict Arnold.
We heard about
your new boyfriend.

32:08.760 --> 32:10.928
Look, Rachel,
we're all happy that you're happy.

32:11.013 --> 32:13.014
But we've worked
too hard in Glee Club...

32:13.098 --> 32:16.100
to let you throw it all away
on a relationship that might
not even be real.

32:16.184 --> 32:18.144
Why, 'cause he's in Vocal Adrenaline?

32:18.228 --> 32:21.022
Their motto is
"Aut neca aut necatus eris,"

32:21.106 --> 32:23.733
which loosely translates
to "murder or be murdered."

32:23.817 --> 32:25.776
They give their dancers
human growth hormone.

32:25.861 --> 32:28.446
- We're not saying
the dude is playing you.
- He's playing you.

32:28.530 --> 32:31.115
We just think
that until regionals are over,

32:31.199 --> 32:33.659
we can't risk
the possibility that he is.

32:33.744 --> 32:36.245
None of us wanna go through
what happened
at sectionals again.

32:36.330 --> 32:41.792
Okay, look, Jesse and I
might not be true love, but what if we are?

32:41.877 --> 32:44.462
I know who I am.

32:44.546 --> 32:47.590
And how many chances at this
am I gonna get?

32:49.176 --> 32:51.135
If you don't break up with him,
you're out.

32:51.219 --> 32:53.137
But you can't kick me out.

32:53.221 --> 32:55.389
But we can all quit if Mr. Schue doesn't.

32:55.474 --> 32:58.392
Well, good luck winning without me.

32:58.477 --> 33:01.270
Everyone is replaceable, even you.

33:01.355 --> 33:05.191
- How could you do this to me?
- How could you do this to us?

33:05.275 --> 33:08.903
We're a team,
and all you've ever wanted
was for us to be great...

33:08.987 --> 33:11.072
and be a part of something special.

33:11.156 --> 33:13.282
Now, is that still true or not?

33:13.367 --> 33:15.409
[School Bell Rings]

33:17.579 --> 33:19.622
[School Bell Rings]

33:22.668 --> 33:24.794
You wanted to see me,
Coach Sylvester?

33:24.878 --> 33:30.675
I did, Rachel. I wanna introduce you
to the Mckinley High Old Maids Club.

33:37.683 --> 33:39.642
Have a seat, boy hips.

33:42.979 --> 33:46.857
I don't understand.
Well, Rachel, it's
come to my attention...

33:46.942 --> 33:50.653
you've been given the old heave-ho
by that terribly uncoordinated
Finn Hudson.

33:50.737 --> 33:53.489
- Ouch.
- And I also understand
you have a serious suitor...

33:53.573 --> 33:56.200
in the form of a piping hot hunk wad
from another district,

33:56.284 --> 34:00.287
but that your fellow Glee Clubbers
are so incensed with betrayal,

34:00.372 --> 34:02.957
they barely have time
to apply Freeze Off...

34:03.083 --> 34:06.961
to the clusters of warts
between their knuckles.
How did you know that?

34:07.087 --> 34:10.506
Britt and I told everybody in Glee Club
about Jesse St. James.
They're furious.

34:10.632 --> 34:14.135
If Rachel falls for him,
the club will self-destruct.
Outstanding. On to step two-

34:14.219 --> 34:17.930
round up a bunch
of mustache-sporting teenage girls
with glandular conditions.

34:18.056 --> 34:21.225
Anything else?
Sometimes I forget
my middle name.

34:21.309 --> 34:23.227
I know how torn
you must be, Berry.

34:23.311 --> 34:26.981
My freshman year,
I fell for a boy on an
opposing wrestling squad,

34:27.065 --> 34:28.983
but my team wouldn't go for it.

34:29.067 --> 34:31.986
So the next time I stepped onto the mat,
I pinned him so hard,

34:32.070 --> 34:34.864
it ruptured his scrotum,
ending his run for the state championship...

34:34.948 --> 34:37.408
and my run for his heart.

34:37.492 --> 34:40.828
To my team, I was a legend.

34:40.912 --> 34:43.456
But I relished this victory
in solitude.

34:43.540 --> 34:48.711
Now I spend my Friday nights
making out with my cat
and watching Ghost Whisperer.

34:48.795 --> 34:52.381
Well, Rachel, if I weren't ignoring
what these ladies were saying...

34:52.466 --> 34:54.967
out of an overwhelming sense
of deep repulsion,

34:55.051 --> 35:00.431
I would probably hear them
encouraging you to go for it
with your Carmel High beau.

35:00.515 --> 35:02.725
Or you might end up like Dottie here,

35:02.809 --> 35:06.145
who, although her father offered a sizable
dowry, which included livestock,

35:06.229 --> 35:08.481
still couldn't get a date to homecoming.

35:08.565 --> 35:12.735
- No homecoming?
- No Valentine's, no sock hop.

35:12.819 --> 35:15.863
Rachel, you need to become
even more narcissistic...

35:15.947 --> 35:17.865
and self-centered than you already are.

35:17.949 --> 35:21.410
Think of yourself,
your potential happiness.

35:21.495 --> 35:23.746
If not,

35:23.830 --> 35:25.831
join the club.

35:35.759 --> 35:38.469
[Door Opens, Closes]

35:38.553 --> 35:41.388
Beautiful table. Meticulous, really.

35:42.599 --> 35:45.017
I guess being crazy has its benefits.

35:47.479 --> 35:49.480
It's date night.

35:49.564 --> 35:52.733
Actually, it was tomorrow,
but Will wanted tonight,
so I'm surprising him.

35:52.818 --> 35:55.736
And I know
he keeps a key under the mat.

35:55.821 --> 35:58.322
You're really loving this, aren't you?

35:58.406 --> 36:01.283
I take no pleasure in your pain, Terri.

36:01.368 --> 36:04.537
But I am enjoying seeing Will
get a second chance at happiness, yes.

36:04.621 --> 36:07.540
Oh, and you're the one to introduce him
to this magical new world of bliss?

36:07.624 --> 36:09.583
What, you with your
three-times-a-day showers...

36:09.668 --> 36:11.544
and the fact that you can't sleep
unless your shoes are all in a row?

36:11.628 --> 36:13.504
Is there a reason that you're here?

36:13.588 --> 36:16.257
'Cause I'd kind of like
you to be gone when Will gets home.

36:18.510 --> 36:21.762
I just need to pick up the rest
of my Bruckheimer DVDs.

36:32.524 --> 36:34.400
Whose is this?

36:34.484 --> 36:37.778
That's mine.
I got really tired of watching
Con Air every night.

36:37.863 --> 36:40.739
And Will picked "Hello" as our song.

36:40.824 --> 36:43.075
Oh, you poor girl.

36:43.159 --> 36:46.078
Don't bother sleeping
with my husband tonight.

36:46.162 --> 36:50.666
You're already screwed.
"Hello" was our prom song.

36:50.750 --> 36:52.710
I doubt Will remembers.

36:52.794 --> 36:55.337
He goes to the market for milk,
comes home with a pack of gum.

36:55.422 --> 36:57.631
You're lying.

37:00.302 --> 37:02.261
Ask him.

37:02.345 --> 37:06.515
Or better yet, go to the library...

37:06.600 --> 37:09.602
and look it up for yourself
in that year's Thunderclap.

37:13.815 --> 37:15.733
Sorry.

37:18.570 --> 37:20.571
Jesse?

37:23.658 --> 37:26.035
Who's there?

37:27.329 --> 37:29.955
- I carry a rape whistle!
- Just me.

37:30.040 --> 37:33.000
- [Sighs]
- Most spots are 2,500 watts.

37:33.084 --> 37:35.461
This one is 10 times brighter.

37:35.545 --> 37:38.005
We have to wear sunscreen on stage,
but it's worth it.

37:38.131 --> 37:42.009
I guess everything
is bigger and brighter here.
[Laughs]

37:43.303 --> 37:45.596
I have to ask you something,

37:45.680 --> 37:47.681
and I need you to tell me the truth,
because if you don't,

37:47.766 --> 37:51.477
there will be consequences—
life-and-death consequences.

37:51.561 --> 37:55.940
Because if I give myself to you
and it turns out that you're just playing me,

37:56.024 --> 37:57.858
I might die.

37:57.943 --> 38:00.861
Not literally, but emotionally.

38:00.946 --> 38:05.199
It'll be the kind of heartbreak that girls
like me hold for the rest of their lives,

38:05.325 --> 38:08.744
like Barbra
in The Way We Were.
[Chuckles] Oh, my God.

38:09.913 --> 38:13.207
What?
You're more of a drama
queen than I am.

38:18.129 --> 38:20.673
Hi. I'm Jesse.

38:20.757 --> 38:22.800
I know who you are.

38:22.884 --> 38:27.554
You know Jesse St. James,
the star of Vocal Adrenaline,
your competition at regionals.

38:27.639 --> 38:30.641
I wanna introduce you to Jesse,

38:30.725 --> 38:33.143
the guy who's nuts about you,

38:33.228 --> 38:35.396
the guy who would never hurt you.

38:45.865 --> 38:47.866
No one can know.

38:48.994 --> 38:50.911
I understand.

39:05.802 --> 39:08.804
- [School Bell Rings]
- Hi.

39:08.888 --> 39:10.806
Hey.

39:12.017 --> 39:13.976
I get home last night,

39:14.060 --> 39:18.731
and it was like some ghost
had laid out this beautiful,
romantic meal for me—

39:18.857 --> 39:22.067
a ghost who wears
your perfume.
I was just in the library.

39:24.237 --> 39:26.363
Page 42.

39:26.448 --> 39:27.906
Okay.

39:27.991 --> 39:32.327
Oh, my- my junior prom.

39:41.921 --> 39:43.922
I wanted to surprise you on Wednesday.

39:44.007 --> 39:49.553
Terri came by and, um, told me
about the prom, about the song.

39:49.637 --> 39:52.681
Emma, I have no feelings
about this night anymore.

39:52.766 --> 39:56.018
- I didn't even remember the song.
- I know, not consciously.

39:57.353 --> 40:00.481
But somewhere inside,
you're still not over her.

40:02.400 --> 40:04.234
We were naive.

40:04.319 --> 40:09.323
I think sometimes we spend
so much time with these kids
that we start acting like them.

40:10.992 --> 40:14.953
You've been in the same relationship
your entire life.

40:15.955 --> 40:17.873
You don't know who you are alone.

40:17.957 --> 40:23.045
I think this song is just the beginning
of you repeating the same patterns.

40:23.129 --> 40:26.715
Terri and I met when I was 15.
I'm a different person now.

40:26.800 --> 40:30.594
How is you compromising
yourself for my crazy...

40:30.678 --> 40:33.388
any different than you doing it for hers?

40:45.068 --> 40:48.362
Well, what do you wanna do?

40:48.446 --> 40:50.989
I think that...

40:52.075 --> 40:54.076
you need to spend some time alone.

40:55.620 --> 40:58.705
I do. I think you need
to get to know yourself.

40:58.790 --> 41:02.084
You haven't been okay
with having your own needs
since you were 15.

41:08.758 --> 41:11.051
You're right.

41:11.136 --> 41:16.014
I guess I'm just not good
at being alone...

41:16.099 --> 41:19.059
and realizing
what my own needs are.

41:21.062 --> 41:24.606
Well, maybe around the time
that you figure out what they are,

41:24.691 --> 41:27.025
maybe I'll be ready to get a little messy.

41:31.364 --> 41:33.365
Can you go now?

41:34.951 --> 41:39.788
I think I need to close the door and cry.
[Laughs, Clears Throat]

42:04.981 --> 42:07.232
[Cries]
[School Bell Rings]

42:08.276 --> 42:10.861
Hey. I ended it with Jesse.

42:10.945 --> 42:13.363
You can spread the word.
I know you know how to do that.

42:13.448 --> 42:15.657
Look, I'm sorry. Uh-

42:15.742 --> 42:19.828
I know this really sucks for you,
but I think it's for the best.

42:19.954 --> 42:24.082
Taking one for the team.
I get it.
No, not just for the team.

42:24.167 --> 42:26.919
For us. You and me.

42:27.003 --> 42:31.381
I've been thinking a lot lately.
I feel like I have all these problems,

42:31.466 --> 42:34.384
you know, with Quinn
and basketball and girls and stuff,

42:34.469 --> 42:37.262
and I've been so overwhelmed
trying to figure them all out.

42:37.347 --> 42:40.432
Then I realized the only thing
I needed to fix was us.

42:42.185 --> 42:47.356
I want us to be together, Rachel,
a real couple.

42:47.440 --> 42:51.318
Look. I even circled some dates
on your crazy calendar.

42:53.071 --> 42:57.616
Is you not being able to talk right now
a good thing or a bad thing?

42:57.742 --> 42:59.785
I can't.
Can't what?

43:00.828 --> 43:03.956
I— I can't be a couple with you.

43:06.125 --> 43:09.002
It's the team.

43:09.087 --> 43:11.797
We— We can't have
any, um, drama right now.

43:11.881 --> 43:15.259
You know, we need—
we need to focus on regionals.

43:15.343 --> 43:17.678
And I appreciate your offer,

43:17.762 --> 43:21.390
but in the spirit
of being a team player,
I have to decline.

43:21.474 --> 43:24.768
Hey, whoa.
[Chuckles]

43:24.852 --> 43:29.898
I'm not just some guy
you met at the music store
that you can just blow off.

43:29.983 --> 43:32.526
I don't give up that easy.

43:35.029 --> 43:37.030
See you in rehearsal.

